That patch applies to the Emerald Mines CD (c) 1994 Kingsoft/Almathera.

This install has the slave-version 1.0.
It needs WHDLoad16 or higher in the path (eg in c:).
For this install you need the Crystal Caverns 4 disk from the Emerald Web at 
http://www.emeraldmines.net/default.asp?action=detail&p=downloads&id=54
an ofcourse your Emerald Mines CD. Unpack the Crystal Caverns disk and
insert the adf in a disk drive, and insert the CD into your CD drive.

Note:    This install uses the engine from No One Inc. and thus allows
           you to save your progress and highscores.

Known Problem: On my UAE, it happens that the Amiga crashes when quitting
           the game. Please file a WHDLoad bug report when that happens
           to you too, so WEPL has some more examples for configurations
           of this bug.

History: V1.0 - 2013-mar-02 Initial slave version.

The install is tested on an 18 MB 68030 and on E-UAE.
It needs 1000 kB Chipmem, 256 kB arbitrary memory and additionally 800 kB
  for preload. It also needs about 100 MB on your hard disk and a lot of
  time to install!

Disclaimer: Install is Freeware and sourcecode is included. 
        You use the install wholly on your own risk.

Full whdload package:	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?.lha
Other installs:		http://www.whdload.de/
Report bugs with the bug report form on that page.

Have fun,
Harry.
